Interesting that you should post this today. I, like many diabetics, am very
carb sensitive in the mornings. 10 gr of carbs is my absolute limit.

This morning I slept in and didn't have time to do my usual sort of
breakfast as I had an early and very important appt. So I tossed some
leftover chicken stew I made the kids last night into the microwave. It had
chicken, celery, onion and garlic (all foods I can tolerate at breakfast
normally) and about 1/4 cup cooked barley. I had a massive bg rise about
half an hour later and one of the worst reactive hypoglycemic episodes while
driving a little while later.

Luckily I was at the point of stopping at a small shop so my son could buy
himself some breakfast. He got me a juice. I have felt bad all day.

I have had a rye cracker often for breakfasts on the run, about 8 gr carb in
the cracker spread with mayo and cold hard boiled egg slices. No problems. I
have never eaten barley for breakfast before and I was shocked at the result
because I eat barley often, with an evening meal. It may well work for
someone with no glucose problems but I have to say it was a big breakfast
loser for me personally. Right up there with oatmeal at breakfast - which
produces the same result.

