Sorry to hear of the hyper and hypo - but I'm not surprised.

I make a vege soup (see the recipe in the blog) with about
three tablespoons of barley in the big pot which makes ten
serves. I found, by experimentation in the past, if I
increase that portion of barley to five tablespoons spread
across the five serves, it raises my BG's an extra full
mmol(18mg/dl) after lunch if the only food eaten is the bowl
of soup.

Cheers, Alan, T2, Australia.
